        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-07-12 12:42:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nWhat is really confusing is why this uses \"microservice config\" model code. My understanding is its a Naming Policy and its a implemented as a decision, not a config. Per Liam's request, we should schedule a meeting to help the reviewers understand this code.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "243de07f490b55af6b401e764520b2b8925b90db",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2757,
          "name": "Praveen Augustus",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pa834y@att.com",
          "username": "pa834y"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-07-12 22:41:09.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThe JSON created during policy creation is same for both existing config MS policies and the new decision MS policies. The existing config MS policy code has been reused as much as possible. \nThe name generation logic in PDP is in new files under org.onap.policy.pdp.rest.api.operations and org.onap.policy.pdp.rest.api.models and starts from org.onap.policy.pdp.rest.api.services.DecisionMsNamingService - run()\nInput => getDecision API request params and JSON data from policy instance.\n\nI'm available anytime next week.\n \n> (1 comment)\n > \n > What is really confusing is why this uses \"microservice config\"\n > model code. My understanding is its a Naming Policy and its a\n > implemented as a decision, not a config. Per Liam's request, we\n > should schedule a meeting to help the reviewers understand this\n > code.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "1078c58a1cb1f1541a2823a5fc4e2b37800b1940",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-07-13 11:56:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(3 comments)\n\nRe-using code is great, but only if it helps reduce cyclomatic complexity and makes sense to developers who want to understand how the code works so they can enhance or fix it.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
